CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 20, 1957, pg. A1, reads: "Distinguished Visitors - Vice President William R. Tolbert Jr. of Liberia, receives the keys to the city from Pittsburgh Councilman Paul F. Jones, substituting for Mayor David L. Lawrence who was out of the city. Liberian Ambassador George A. Padmore extreme right, and John T. Owens, assistant general counselor of Columbia-Southern Chemical Company, observes."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh City Councilman Paul F. Jones presenting key to the city to Vice President of Liberia William R. Tolbert Jr., with others, including John T. Owens and Liberian Ambassador George A. Padmore standing on left, in Office of the Mayor at City County Building
